records.addlTxt:
The State moves to amend the charge to 4th degree sexual assault, contrary to Section 940.225(3m) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
3) Obtain high school diploma or its equivalent;
4) Defendant is to comply with any court order entered into if he is found to be, and adjudicated, the father of the child;
5) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
6) No contact with the victim without prior approval from the agent with the exception being birth, care and custody on the minor child;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
8) Pay court costs;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
Minutes.
